WEBVTT

00:04.134 --> 00:04.352
.

00:04.395 --> 00:07.442
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:07.485 --> 00:10.880
- Isiah is Gavin.
And he needs your help.

00:10.923 --> 00:14.710
- There was a portal on top
of a mountain in Topanga.

00:14.753 --> 00:16.668
And it leads to 1988.

00:16.712 --> 00:20.498
If Isiah doesn't make it,
your children will die.

00:20.542 --> 00:23.153
- There's something very
important I need you to do.

00:23.197 --> 00:24.850
- I need you to take me
to Topanga.

00:24.894 --> 00:26.243
We have to leave now.

00:26.287 --> 00:28.332
<i>- I saw this rock </i>
in that world.

00:28.376 --> 00:30.247
<i>And someone called me </i>
by a different name.

00:30.291 --> 00:31.770
- What was it?
- Lilly.

00:31.814 --> 00:33.772
- They're sinkhole locations.
Look at this.

00:33.816 --> 00:35.122
And according to this map,

00:35.165 --> 00:36.688
the one in Seattle is
gonna open tomorrow.

00:36.732 --> 00:39.169
- The ravine ends four miles
east of here.

00:39.213 --> 00:42.390
Bring Isiah there
or I'll kill 'em both.

00:42.433 --> 00:44.522
- Eve, wait.
You shouldn't go alone.

00:44.566 --> 00:48.048
- I don't have a choice.
I have to save my son.

00:48.091 --> 00:51.051
<i>[tense music]</i>

00:51.094 --> 00:58.232
<i>♪ </i>

01:06.718 --> 01:09.330
- What are we gonna do?
- We're gonna be fine.

01:09.373 --> 01:10.853
Just stay calm.

01:10.896 --> 01:12.985
- Calm?
Are you kidding?

01:13.029 --> 01:14.770
- Josh,
just take a breath, okay?

01:14.813 --> 01:17.207
<i>♪ </i>

01:17.251 --> 01:18.556
I know you're angry with me.

01:18.600 --> 01:22.082
But we can't focus
on that right now.

01:22.125 --> 01:25.607
Josh, I never meant
to hurt you.

01:25.650 --> 01:28.697
Or your dad.

01:28.740 --> 01:31.917
I really am sorry.

01:31.961 --> 01:34.920
Silas, look!

01:34.964 --> 01:37.880
<i>♪ </i>

01:37.923 --> 01:39.708
Mom!

01:39.751 --> 01:43.842
<i>♪ </i>

01:43.886 --> 01:45.801
Where's Isiah?

01:45.844 --> 01:48.108
He's somewhere safe.

01:48.151 --> 01:51.285
- I told you what would happen
if you didn't bring him to me.

01:51.328 --> 01:52.460
- If I don't get Isiah
through the light,

01:52.503 --> 01:54.940
my children will die.

01:54.984 --> 01:57.943
I know.

01:57.987 --> 02:00.685
But I won't sacrifice
my family to save yours.

02:00.729 --> 02:02.557
Isiah is all I have.

02:02.600 --> 02:04.776
- This isn't just
about my family.

02:04.820 --> 02:09.129
Isiah is Gavin.
Josh is your great grandson.

02:09.172 --> 02:13.350
Doesn't change anything.

02:13.394 --> 02:17.354
- This is about more than
just Isiah, isn't it?

02:17.398 --> 02:21.184
You're not from that village.
You know Aldridge.

02:21.228 --> 02:23.186
So who are you?
Who are you really?

02:23.230 --> 02:26.276
<i>♪ </i>

02:26.320 --> 02:29.410
- Tie her up.
- Grab her.

02:29.453 --> 02:31.281
- No, wait.
Wait, no!

02:31.325 --> 02:34.197
<i>♪ </i>

02:34.241 --> 02:36.634
Find Isiah.

02:36.678 --> 02:43.598
<i>♪ </i>

02:44.729 --> 02:47.210
- You guys all right?
- We're fine.

02:47.254 --> 02:49.125
- How are we gonna
get out of here?

02:49.169 --> 02:51.171
- Don't worry.
I got a plan.

02:51.214 --> 02:54.435
<i>♪ </i>

02:54.478 --> 02:57.177
You wanted to be caught.

02:57.220 --> 03:01.746
<i>♪ </i>

03:01.790 --> 03:04.836
- The light in Topanga closes
in 12 hours.

03:04.880 --> 03:07.230
Whoever's going needs
to leave now.

03:07.274 --> 03:09.363
- Just so we're
super clear here,

03:09.406 --> 03:11.930
whoever wants to go,
just has to walk through it,

03:11.974 --> 03:14.846
and boom, you're in 1988?

03:14.890 --> 03:16.239
Simple as that.

03:16.283 --> 03:17.675
- How are we supposed
to find it?

03:17.719 --> 03:18.937
I don't see a light in the sky.

03:18.981 --> 03:20.548
- It's because it's not
in the sky.

03:20.591 --> 03:22.506
You can't see it
from the ground.

03:22.550 --> 03:25.030
Head northwest ten miles.

03:25.074 --> 03:27.903
The light will be at
the highest peak in that area.

03:27.946 --> 03:30.166
- How the hell do you
know any of this?

03:30.210 --> 03:32.603
<i>♪ </i>

03:32.647 --> 03:35.040
- Because I'm responsible
for these sinkholes opening.

03:35.084 --> 03:37.695
<i>♪ </i>

03:37.739 --> 03:39.306
Hold on.

03:39.349 --> 03:42.613
You're saying you're the reason
we're all stuck down here?

03:42.657 --> 03:44.354
- We never meant
for this to happen.

03:44.398 --> 03:48.967
- We?
Who are the others?

03:49.011 --> 03:51.318
- One of the people
involved is Silas,

03:51.361 --> 03:53.058
Isiah's grandfather.

03:53.102 --> 03:55.365
We're scientists by trade.

03:55.409 --> 03:56.845
We both made some mistakes

03:56.888 --> 03:59.369
that we're trying to correct
in our own ways.

03:59.413 --> 04:03.025
The portal at Topanga
is a way out.

04:03.068 --> 04:06.028
I owe you that at least.

04:06.071 --> 04:07.769
You're telling the truth.

04:07.812 --> 04:10.902
<i>♪ </i>

04:10.946 --> 04:14.297
I'm going.

04:14.341 --> 04:17.474
Then so am I.

04:17.518 --> 04:20.564
- Look, I'm happy to bring
a group to the mountain.

04:20.608 --> 04:23.219
But Riley and I
are staying here.

04:23.263 --> 04:25.352
- Sure about that?
- Yeah.

04:25.395 --> 04:26.788
- We're not giving up
on going home.

04:26.831 --> 04:28.790
Neither are we.

04:28.833 --> 04:30.400
Sam!

04:30.444 --> 04:31.880
- Ty.
- Hey.

04:31.923 --> 04:33.229
What's going on?

04:33.273 --> 04:34.404
- Josh and Levi were taken
by Silas

04:34.448 --> 04:35.753
and three men from the village.

04:35.797 --> 04:37.015
What?

04:37.059 --> 04:38.582
- If any of you can help,
we need to go now.

04:38.626 --> 04:40.149
Why would they take them?

04:40.192 --> 04:42.151
- And who are you?
- This is Paara.

04:42.194 --> 04:43.413
She's a friend
from the village.

04:43.457 --> 04:45.415
Look, we'll explain
everything on the way.

04:45.459 --> 04:46.764
But Eve needs our help.

04:46.808 --> 04:49.245
- All right, let's go.
- I'll be right back.

04:49.289 --> 04:50.986
- Hey, now would be a good time
to give me back my gun.

04:51.029 --> 04:53.293
You got it.

04:53.336 --> 04:55.338
You coming?

04:55.382 --> 04:58.820
Uh...

04:58.863 --> 05:01.605
- Someone should stay,
look after Aldridge.

05:01.649 --> 05:04.042
Scott, can you do that?

05:04.086 --> 05:06.262
Yeah, of course.

05:06.306 --> 05:09.134
<i>♪ </i>

05:09.178 --> 05:10.788
Where did you get that?

05:10.832 --> 05:15.140
- I brought this with me
for a much different reason.

05:15.184 --> 05:18.100
I don't intend to use it unless
it's absolutely necessary.

05:18.143 --> 05:21.146
- Listen, we can help Eve
and get to the mountain.

05:21.190 --> 05:23.018
But we need to leave now.
Who's coming with us?

05:23.061 --> 05:24.367
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

05:24.411 --> 05:26.413
Let's go.

05:26.456 --> 05:30.330
<i>♪ </i>

05:31.505 --> 05:33.071
Hurry up, Veronica.

05:33.115 --> 05:35.465
- We've been walking for hours.
I need a break.

05:35.509 --> 05:36.945
We can't stop.

05:36.988 --> 05:39.469
Rebecca said I have
to get the map to Isiah.

05:39.513 --> 05:41.428
- Why is this
so important to you?

05:41.471 --> 05:44.561
I promised Rebecca I'd do it.

05:44.605 --> 05:49.392
- A promise to a person
you just met?

05:49.436 --> 05:51.873
What's really going on, Lilly?

05:53.918 --> 05:58.401
- Rebecca told me,
if I did this,

05:58.445 --> 06:01.012
she'd help me find a way
back to my family.

06:03.450 --> 06:06.453
- So you were just gonna
leave me behind?

06:06.496 --> 06:08.368
I just thought that,
when we got to Topanga,

06:08.411 --> 06:09.847
you and I could go to 1988.

06:09.891 --> 06:13.155
We could start over together.

06:13.198 --> 06:15.418
I'm not going to 1988.

06:15.462 --> 06:19.727
<i>[soft music]</i>

06:19.770 --> 06:24.035
What Aaron did to us

06:24.079 --> 06:26.951
was awful.

06:26.995 --> 06:29.389
And I know you want
to put it behind you.

06:29.432 --> 06:31.652
<i>♪ </i>

06:31.695 --> 06:36.352
But it brought us together.

06:36.396 --> 06:38.267
You're all I have now, Lilly.

06:38.310 --> 06:41.270
<i>♪ </i>

06:41.313 --> 06:45.579
- I miss my family, Veronica,
my real family.

06:45.622 --> 06:48.451
<i>♪ </i>

06:48.495 --> 06:52.020
Please,
you have to understand.

06:52.063 --> 06:58.983
<i>♪ </i>

07:01.943 --> 07:04.424
- Ahh!
- Veronica!

07:04.467 --> 07:05.468
- What is this?
- Get it off!

07:05.512 --> 07:08.079
Get it off.

07:08.123 --> 07:10.995
Hang on.

07:11.039 --> 07:13.433
Get it off!

07:13.476 --> 07:15.260
It's okay.

07:15.304 --> 07:17.959
I'm gonna get you out of this.

07:18.002 --> 07:20.962
<i>[tense music]</i>

07:21.005 --> 07:27.925
<i>♪ </i>

07:29.449 --> 07:32.582
Isiah, come with me.

07:32.626 --> 07:36.194
- Get off me!
Get off!

07:36.238 --> 07:40.024
[grunting]

07:40.068 --> 07:46.335
<i>♪ </i>

07:46.378 --> 07:48.250
- It's okay.
I'm here to help.

07:48.293 --> 07:49.643
[whistles]

07:49.686 --> 07:53.124
<i>♪ </i>

07:53.168 --> 07:56.345
Isiah.

07:56.388 --> 07:58.521
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

07:58.565 --> 08:01.959
- Okay.
- Hey, where's Eve?

08:02.003 --> 08:04.135
- She said she
couldn't wait anymore.

08:04.179 --> 08:09.489
<i>♪ </i>

08:09.532 --> 08:11.534
Down, down.

08:11.578 --> 08:14.450
<i>♪ </i>

08:14.494 --> 08:16.626
We take them by surprise.

08:16.670 --> 08:18.280
Ty, Paara, you're with me.

08:18.323 --> 08:21.239
- What about the rest of us?
- Get Isiah to Topanga.

08:21.283 --> 08:22.502
Just head northwest.

08:22.545 --> 08:23.807
We can't just leave.

08:23.851 --> 08:27.768
Riley, I know you want
to help Josh.

08:27.811 --> 08:31.162
This is how you do it, okay?

08:31.206 --> 08:33.121
Stay low.

08:33.164 --> 08:35.558
<i>♪ </i>

08:35.602 --> 08:40.128
- I'm scared, Paara.
- You have to be strong.

08:40.171 --> 08:41.912
- We'll catch up with you
as soon as we can.

08:41.956 --> 08:44.480
- Yeah, keep your head down.
Keep your head down.

08:44.524 --> 08:47.352
Go, go, go, go, go.

08:47.396 --> 08:54.316
<i>♪ </i>

08:55.709 --> 08:58.189
Almost there, keep going.

08:58.233 --> 08:59.756
Come on.

08:59.800 --> 09:06.937
<i>♪ </i>

09:12.421 --> 09:18.209
[grunting]

09:18.253 --> 09:21.343
<i>♪ </i>

09:21.386 --> 09:23.475
Come on.

09:23.519 --> 09:24.738
Here.

09:24.781 --> 09:28.611
<i>♪ </i>

09:28.655 --> 09:30.439
Stop!

09:30.482 --> 09:37.577
<i>♪ </i>

09:38.621 --> 09:40.623
- Silas!
- He's getting away!

09:40.667 --> 09:42.407
Stop!

09:42.451 --> 09:45.019
- [groans]
- Josh, hey, hey.

09:45.062 --> 09:47.238
Hey, hey, what's going on?
What's going on--talk to me.

09:47.282 --> 09:50.894
- It's this weird pain shooting
through my whole body.

09:50.938 --> 09:54.506
I've never felt
anything like it.

09:54.550 --> 09:57.771
Eve, what's going on?

09:57.814 --> 09:59.642
- Aldridge said,
once the light begins to close,

09:59.686 --> 10:02.863
Josh and Izzy will start
to feel sick.

10:02.906 --> 10:04.734
It's happening.

10:04.778 --> 10:11.915
<i>♪ </i>

10:16.572 --> 10:18.748
- There's gonna be
a sinkhole in Seattle.

10:18.792 --> 10:21.185
- So what's the plan?
- We've got to get there.

10:21.229 --> 10:24.624
There's still a chance
we can save Mom and Josh.

10:24.667 --> 10:27.061
I'll book us
on the next flight.

10:27.104 --> 10:30.891
<i>[tense music]</i>

10:30.934 --> 10:33.067
I'm coming with you.

10:33.110 --> 10:34.982
Are you sure?

10:35.025 --> 10:36.984
- There may be more
that I remember,

10:37.027 --> 10:38.725
something that can help you.

10:38.768 --> 10:44.208
Besides, something tells me
I need to see this through.

10:44.252 --> 10:46.689
Okay.

10:46.733 --> 10:48.473
Does the map say where

10:48.517 --> 10:50.650
in Seattle the sinkhole
is going to open?

10:50.693 --> 10:54.610
- Yeah. There, near the mouth
of the Duwamish River.

10:54.654 --> 10:59.441
- The Duwamish River?
- What's wrong?

10:59.484 --> 11:01.312
- Well, that's in the center
of downtown.

11:01.356 --> 11:02.574
Everyone there is in danger.

11:02.618 --> 11:04.185
- It's not just downtown,
Gavin.

11:04.228 --> 11:06.361
The entire city could be
in danger.

11:06.404 --> 11:08.406
We don't know
how accurate this map is.

11:08.450 --> 11:10.191
The sinkhole could open
anywhere in the area.

11:10.234 --> 11:13.281
- We need to warn everyone,
get them to evacuate the city.

11:13.324 --> 11:15.239
- Our proof is a map
from 10,000 BC.

11:15.283 --> 11:18.242
No one's gonna believe us.

11:18.286 --> 11:20.331
There's one person who might.

11:20.375 --> 11:22.638
<i>♪ </i>

11:22.682 --> 11:24.292
- You sure you think
this is a good idea?

11:24.335 --> 11:25.946
We don't have another option.

11:25.989 --> 11:28.905
<i>♪ </i>

11:28.949 --> 11:30.951
- Dad.
- Iz?

11:30.994 --> 11:34.519
Iz, are you okay?

11:34.563 --> 11:37.087
- What's wrong?
- I don't know.

11:37.131 --> 11:38.959
I don't know.

11:39.002 --> 11:45.139
<i>♪ </i>

11:45.182 --> 11:47.924
- We lost Silas.
- How you doing?

11:47.968 --> 11:49.796
- We have to get Isiah
through the light.

11:49.839 --> 11:51.667
- He's safe--I sent him ahead
with Marybeth to the mountain.

11:51.711 --> 11:53.930
- No, he's not safe,
not with Silas still out there.

11:53.974 --> 11:56.628
He's gonna go to the mountain.
He's gonna try and stop Isiah.

11:56.672 --> 11:58.021
- And he has a head
start on us.

11:58.065 --> 11:59.283
There's another way,

11:59.327 --> 12:01.677
a shortcut
through a network of caves.

12:01.721 --> 12:02.983
They'll bring you
to the summit.

12:03.026 --> 12:04.549
Where is it?

12:04.593 --> 12:06.508
- The entrance is near the
eastern base of the mountain,

12:06.551 --> 12:09.163
in the middle of a field
by a fallen tree.

12:09.206 --> 12:10.599
But there are dangers there.

12:10.642 --> 12:12.688
Many years ago, there was
a village near the caves.

12:12.732 --> 12:15.082
They were protective
of their territory.

12:15.125 --> 12:17.432
The area is still filled
with traps.

12:17.475 --> 12:18.868
- Well, we'll take our chances.
- Yeah.

12:18.912 --> 12:20.391
Catch up with Isiah,

12:20.435 --> 12:21.479
and we'll take him
to the caves.

12:21.523 --> 12:22.611
What about Silas?

12:22.654 --> 12:24.265
Does he know
about the shortcut?

12:24.308 --> 12:26.658
- Yes, but it's too dangerous
to go alone.

12:26.702 --> 12:29.313
He'll take the longer route
up the side of the mountain.

12:29.357 --> 12:30.793
I'll go after him.

12:30.837 --> 12:33.317
I'm coming with you.

12:33.361 --> 12:34.710
You good?

12:34.754 --> 12:38.061
- Yeah, it's painful.
But I can walk.

12:38.105 --> 12:39.410
All right, we better move.

12:39.454 --> 12:42.849
<i>♪ </i>

12:42.892 --> 12:44.241
Sam told me,

12:44.285 --> 12:46.504
"Stay here.
Look after Aldridge."

12:46.548 --> 12:49.812
And I didn't even object.
My bud Josh is in trouble.

12:49.856 --> 12:51.988
And I did nothing.

12:52.032 --> 12:54.425
After everything
I've been through, deep down,

12:54.469 --> 12:57.951
I'm still
the same scared coward,

12:57.994 --> 12:59.343
a freakin' coward.

12:59.387 --> 13:01.302
- [mooing]
- Oh, sorry.

13:01.345 --> 13:04.696
No, I'm not yelling at you.
I'm just mad at myself.

13:04.740 --> 13:07.003
Excuse me.

13:07.047 --> 13:08.657
Uh...

13:08.700 --> 13:11.573
- I thought
you were resting.

13:11.616 --> 13:16.273
- There's somewhere I need
to go a few miles from here.

13:16.317 --> 13:18.667
I was hoping
you'd help me get there.

13:18.710 --> 13:20.190
- Uh-huh.

13:20.234 --> 13:24.238
I suppose you're not gonna
tell me what this is about.

13:24.281 --> 13:26.501
What you said about being
responsible for the sinkholes,

13:26.544 --> 13:28.024
that's just the tip
of the iceberg, isn't it?

13:28.068 --> 13:30.070
Please, it's very important.

13:30.113 --> 13:33.247
<i>♪ </i>

13:33.290 --> 13:34.857
- You know, I watch
a lot of sci-fi.

13:34.901 --> 13:36.641
And there's always
a character like you.

13:36.685 --> 13:38.730
- Is that right?
- Yeah.

13:38.774 --> 13:41.255
Someone who knows
more than they let on,

13:41.298 --> 13:42.647
doesn't tell anyone anything.

13:42.691 --> 13:44.693
Usually, they're the bad guy.

13:44.736 --> 13:46.782
You think I'm the bad guy?

13:46.826 --> 13:50.612
- I don't know what to think
about anything here.

13:50.655 --> 13:53.789
There are so many
strange things.

13:53.833 --> 13:56.357
Like, why does this cow
have a serial number?

13:56.400 --> 13:57.749
It's lunacy.

13:57.793 --> 14:00.274
Then I'll make you a deal.

14:00.317 --> 14:02.058
You get me to where
I need to go,

14:02.102 --> 14:05.409
and I will give you all
the answers you're looking for.

14:05.453 --> 14:06.802
Or you can do nothing,

14:06.846 --> 14:09.109
and things can stay
exactly as they are.

14:09.152 --> 14:11.894
<i>♪ </i>

14:11.938 --> 14:13.374
When do we leave?

14:13.417 --> 14:19.380
<i>♪ </i>

14:19.423 --> 14:20.816
Where are they?

14:20.860 --> 14:22.470
They should have caught up
to us by now.

14:22.513 --> 14:25.516
- Relax, they'll be fine.
- What if they're not?

14:25.560 --> 14:27.997
- We should go back.
They might need our help.

14:28.041 --> 14:29.912
We need to keep moving.

14:32.610 --> 14:36.876
Hand over the boy.

14:36.919 --> 14:39.791
Take Isiah, run.

14:39.835 --> 14:43.317
- Come on, come on, come on.
Let's go.

14:43.360 --> 14:44.971
Your move, pal.

14:45.014 --> 14:47.843
<i>♪ </i>

14:47.887 --> 14:50.106
[grunting]

14:50.150 --> 14:52.326
Ahh!

14:52.369 --> 14:58.288
[both grunting]

14:58.332 --> 15:05.339
<i>♪ </i>

15:05.382 --> 15:07.254
- [grunts]
Ah!

15:07.297 --> 15:13.260
[grunting]

15:13.303 --> 15:16.176
[gun fires]

15:16.219 --> 15:19.701
You guys all right?

15:19.744 --> 15:22.443
Yeah, I think so.

15:22.486 --> 15:24.880
[groans]

15:24.924 --> 15:27.187
<i>♪ </i>

15:27.230 --> 15:29.015
Marybeth.

15:29.058 --> 15:36.022
<i>♪ </i>

15:43.203 --> 15:47.207
- How you feeling?
- Not great.

15:47.250 --> 15:49.513
So Josh is going through
the same thing right now?

15:49.557 --> 15:52.603
- Yeah, I think so.
Iz, listen.

15:52.647 --> 15:55.998
- Please don't say
it's gonna be okay, Dad.

15:56.042 --> 15:58.522
You don't know that.

15:58.566 --> 16:01.525
<i>[tense music]</i>

16:01.569 --> 16:08.054
<i>♪ </i>

16:08.097 --> 16:10.447
- Markman, thanks
for meeting us.

16:10.491 --> 16:12.058
There's gonna be
another sinkhole,

16:12.101 --> 16:13.885
this time in Seattle.

16:13.929 --> 16:15.975
We need you
to evacuate the city.

16:16.018 --> 16:18.716
<i>♪ </i>

16:18.760 --> 16:22.677
- Where'd you get this?
- From that place down there.

16:22.720 --> 16:24.374
- So you're asking me
to evacuate a city

16:24.418 --> 16:26.550
based on a map from 10,000 BC?

16:26.594 --> 16:28.378
- Are you serious?
- It's not just that.

16:28.422 --> 16:30.380
The seismic readings in Seattle
are the exact same

16:30.424 --> 16:32.469
as before
the La Brea sinkhole opened.

16:32.513 --> 16:34.036
- The city sits
on a fault line.

16:34.080 --> 16:35.690
It could be nothing.

16:35.733 --> 16:38.040
- It's concentrated downtown,
Adam, just like the map says.

16:38.084 --> 16:39.520
We need to clear the area.

16:39.563 --> 16:42.566
This is going to happen
in the next few hours.

16:42.610 --> 16:45.221
- Do you realize the resources
and manpower required

16:45.265 --> 16:46.701
to pull something
like this off?

16:46.744 --> 16:49.399
I make that call and we're
wrong, my career is over.

16:49.443 --> 16:51.271
- We're just trying
to prevent another disaster.

16:51.314 --> 16:54.187
If we're right, and you
do nothing, people will die.

16:54.230 --> 16:55.927
- We can stop
that from happening.

16:55.971 --> 16:58.408
But only if you help us.

16:58.452 --> 17:02.630
<i>♪ </i>

17:02.673 --> 17:05.763
[screaming]

17:05.807 --> 17:09.898
[groaning]

17:09.941 --> 17:11.639
Lilly, that's not gonna work.

17:11.682 --> 17:13.467
I can do this.

17:13.510 --> 17:15.904
No, you can't.

17:15.947 --> 17:19.038
Lilly.

17:19.081 --> 17:21.083
Stop!

17:21.127 --> 17:22.563
- Maybe
I can find a bigger rock.

17:22.606 --> 17:25.000
Look at me.

17:26.480 --> 17:30.049
You don't have time for this.

17:30.092 --> 17:32.094
<i>♪ </i>

17:32.138 --> 17:33.965
The light's gonna close.

17:34.009 --> 17:35.750
Come...

17:35.793 --> 17:37.839
come here.

17:37.882 --> 17:42.104
<i>[soft music]</i>

17:42.148 --> 17:45.499
- I can't leave you here.
- You have to.

17:45.542 --> 17:47.979
<i>♪ </i>

17:48.023 --> 17:51.287
Take the map to Isiah,

17:51.331 --> 17:54.508
so you can get back
to your family.

17:54.551 --> 17:57.119
<i>♪ </i>

17:57.163 --> 18:00.688
Please, you need to go.

18:00.731 --> 18:03.821
<i>♪ </i>

18:03.865 --> 18:06.172
I'll come back for you.

18:06.215 --> 18:08.304
As soon as I get this to him,
I'll come back.

18:08.348 --> 18:11.002
- Mm-hmm.
- I promise.

18:11.046 --> 18:15.006
<i>♪ </i>

18:15.050 --> 18:17.400
[both sobbing]

18:17.444 --> 18:21.535
- I'm sorry
for everything I did.

18:21.578 --> 18:25.278
<i>♪ </i>

18:25.321 --> 18:30.848
I hope one day
you can forgive me.

18:30.892 --> 18:36.550
<i>♪ </i>

18:36.593 --> 18:39.727
Go, go.

18:39.770 --> 18:46.734
<i>♪ </i>

18:54.916 --> 18:56.874
Okay.

18:56.918 --> 18:58.354
It's pretty deep.

18:58.398 --> 18:59.660
You could be bleeding
internally.

18:59.703 --> 19:01.009
We need to get you back
to the clearing.

19:01.052 --> 19:02.358
Believe it or not,

19:02.402 --> 19:04.360
this isn't the first time
I've been stabbed.

19:04.404 --> 19:06.101
- Why don't you take Isiah
over there?

19:06.145 --> 19:07.842
He doesn't need to see this.

19:10.714 --> 19:12.455
Sit there.

19:12.499 --> 19:13.891
Hey.

19:13.935 --> 19:16.720
<i>♪ </i>

19:16.764 --> 19:19.854
I was really worried about you.
Are you okay?

19:19.897 --> 19:21.943
Pushing through it.

19:21.986 --> 19:23.640
I'll be all right.

19:23.684 --> 19:25.555
<i>♪ </i>

19:25.599 --> 19:28.732
- Hey, Marybeth.
You need to listen to Sam.

19:28.776 --> 19:30.560
- We don't have time
to get back to the clearing.

19:30.604 --> 19:31.996
As soon as I go
through that light,

19:32.040 --> 19:33.563
I will go straight
to the hospital.

19:33.607 --> 19:35.870
- We still have
a long ways to go.

19:35.913 --> 19:37.611
You sure you can make it?

19:37.654 --> 19:40.179
- I'll go slow.
I'll be okay.

19:40.222 --> 19:42.006
<i>♪ </i>

19:42.050 --> 19:43.704
Guys, I am not missing
my chance

19:43.747 --> 19:45.967
to get out of this place.

19:46.010 --> 19:47.534
You go ahead.

19:47.577 --> 19:49.579
You don't have
to go at my pace.

19:49.623 --> 19:52.103
Marybeth.

19:52.147 --> 19:55.237
- Don't worry.
I'll stay with her,

19:55.281 --> 19:57.935
make sure she gets there
in one piece.

19:57.979 --> 20:04.246
<i>♪ </i>

20:04.290 --> 20:08.642
- Go, save your family.
I'll be right behind you.

20:08.685 --> 20:11.253
- Take care of her.
- Yeah.

20:11.297 --> 20:18.129
<i>♪ </i>

20:18.173 --> 20:21.916
He can't be that far ahead.

20:21.959 --> 20:25.746
We're going to find Silas.
We are going to stop him.

20:25.789 --> 20:28.923
- I should have
never trusted him.

20:28.966 --> 20:31.795
He put my people in danger.

20:31.839 --> 20:34.842
- The people who helped him
made their own decisions.

20:34.885 --> 20:37.975
That's out of your control.

20:38.019 --> 20:42.153
<i>[tense music]</i>

20:42.197 --> 20:44.678
- [groans]
- Over here.

20:44.721 --> 20:51.250
<i>♪ </i>

20:51.293 --> 20:55.428
- It's painful.
- I'm sorry.

20:55.471 --> 20:59.345
Could the doctors
in 1988 help you?

20:59.388 --> 21:02.391
They don't have a cure.

21:02.435 --> 21:04.524
But maybe their machines

21:04.567 --> 21:07.309
and drugs can make
the end more comfortable.

21:07.353 --> 21:13.837
<i>♪ </i>

21:13.881 --> 21:17.363
- Then perhaps you should
go back to your world.

21:17.406 --> 21:21.236
But I think it would be
for the best.

21:21.280 --> 21:23.717
We should keep moving.

21:23.760 --> 21:30.724
<i>♪ </i>

21:35.772 --> 21:37.208
How you doing?

21:37.252 --> 21:40.647
- Still hurts, but I'm okay.
Just thinking about Izzy.

21:40.690 --> 21:44.085
Yeah, she's with your dad.

21:44.128 --> 21:46.566
He's gonna take care of her.

21:49.264 --> 21:51.571
I know he is.

21:51.614 --> 21:53.703
Few days ago, I never
would have believed that,

21:53.747 --> 21:57.272
but now...

21:59.405 --> 22:02.059
I miss him.

22:02.103 --> 22:04.018
Me too.

22:05.846 --> 22:10.546
<i>♪ </i>

22:10.590 --> 22:14.071
- It's the tree Paara
told us about.

22:14.115 --> 22:16.247
- Remember, Paara said
this place is dangerous.

22:16.291 --> 22:17.510
Let's keep our eyes peeled.

22:17.553 --> 22:19.294
- Riley and I
will take the lead.

22:19.338 --> 22:20.687
Levi and Josh,
you bring up the rear.

22:20.730 --> 22:24.212
- No, it's all right.
I'll stay with Isiah.

22:24.255 --> 22:30.958
<i>♪ </i>

22:33.830 --> 22:36.093
- You want to tell me
what that was about?

22:36.137 --> 22:39.532
<i>♪ </i>

22:39.575 --> 22:42.883
Josh knows about us.

22:42.926 --> 22:44.406
- I can't deal
with this right now.

22:44.450 --> 22:46.365
I just have to focus on Isiah.

22:46.408 --> 22:52.588
<i>♪ </i>

22:52.632 --> 22:57.245
- If I make it to 1988,
you'll be okay, right?

22:57.288 --> 23:00.988
I think so.

23:01.031 --> 23:03.251
Look, I know you're scared.

23:03.294 --> 23:04.905
I'd be freaking out, too.

23:04.948 --> 23:09.431
But the person
you grow up to be...

23:11.172 --> 23:13.304
He's pretty great.

23:13.348 --> 23:15.959
- Really?
- Yeah.

23:16.003 --> 23:18.222
<i>♪ </i>

23:18.266 --> 23:21.138
One day,
you're gonna be a pilot.

23:21.182 --> 23:23.358
You're gonna fly.

23:23.402 --> 23:26.622
- Like a bird?
- Yeah.

23:26.666 --> 23:28.537
And you're gonna love it.

23:28.581 --> 23:31.932
- It's a dead end.
This way.

23:31.975 --> 23:34.064
<i>♪ </i>

23:34.108 --> 23:36.327
Look, it's a tar pit.

23:36.371 --> 23:40.767
<i>♪ </i>

23:40.810 --> 23:43.204
- Must be the way
up the mountain.

23:43.247 --> 23:44.988
This should be fun.

23:45.032 --> 23:49.689
<i>♪ </i>

23:53.997 --> 23:57.610
- Could be a trap.
- Climb up, ladder breaks.

23:57.653 --> 24:01.222
Even if you survive the fall,
you're stuck in the tar.

24:01.265 --> 24:03.006
- We don't really have
another choice.

24:03.050 --> 24:04.443
All right, who's going first?

24:04.486 --> 24:05.618
- I should go before
the pain comes back.

24:05.661 --> 24:07.097
Josh.

24:07.141 --> 24:08.403
- We don't even know
if it can support your weight.

24:08.447 --> 24:10.492
- Only one way to find out.
- Josh, no!

24:10.536 --> 24:12.799
No, no!

24:12.842 --> 24:15.541
Please be careful.

24:15.584 --> 24:17.804
Grab the ladder.

24:17.847 --> 24:19.675
<i>[tense music]</i>

24:19.719 --> 24:20.763
- You got it?
- Yeah.

24:20.807 --> 24:22.809
Go.

24:22.852 --> 24:24.506
[grunts]

24:24.550 --> 24:29.337
<i>♪ </i>

24:29.380 --> 24:30.773
Easy, easy.

24:30.817 --> 24:36.910
<i>♪ </i>

24:36.953 --> 24:38.825
You're almost there.

24:38.868 --> 24:41.654
<i>♪ </i>

24:41.697 --> 24:43.438
I made it.

24:43.482 --> 24:45.658
Oh, God.

24:45.701 --> 24:52.621
<i>♪ </i>

24:56.016 --> 24:57.408
You need a break?

24:57.452 --> 25:00.368
I'm fine.

25:00.411 --> 25:02.936
Keep moving.
Just a little dizzy.

25:03.980 --> 25:06.679
<i>♪ </i>

25:06.722 --> 25:08.202
Oh, Jesus, Marybeth!

25:08.245 --> 25:11.553
Hey, hey, hey, wake up.
Wake up, hey.

25:11.597 --> 25:12.989
There you are.

25:13.033 --> 25:15.992
<i>♪ </i>

25:16.036 --> 25:19.692
- Sam was right.
It's worse than I thought.

25:19.735 --> 25:22.433
- Here.
Easy, easy, easy.

25:22.477 --> 25:26.699
Hey, listen to me.
Listen to me.

25:26.742 --> 25:28.527
Hey, we need to get you
to a hospital, okay?

25:28.570 --> 25:31.094
The only way to do that
is through that light.

25:31.138 --> 25:32.705
- Lucas, I don't think
I'm gonna make it.

25:32.748 --> 25:34.402
But you need to go.
You don't have much time.

25:34.445 --> 25:37.057
- No, no, no way.
I'll carry you if I have to.

25:37.100 --> 25:38.580
- You can't carry me
up a mountain.

25:38.624 --> 25:39.712
I can damn well try.

25:39.755 --> 25:41.061
- And then we'll both
be stuck here.

25:41.104 --> 25:42.410
You got a chance
to get out of this place.

25:42.453 --> 25:43.933
- I don't want you to lose it.
- No.

25:43.977 --> 25:45.587
- [groans]
What the hell are you doing?

25:45.631 --> 25:49.112
- I'm getting us out of here.
Hey, do not argue, all right?

25:49.156 --> 25:52.072
This is not a negotiation.
Come on.

25:52.115 --> 25:53.900
<i>♪ </i>

25:53.943 --> 25:56.903
You got it, buddy.

25:56.946 --> 25:59.558
Come on.
You're almost there.

25:59.601 --> 26:01.908
Don't look down, okay?

26:01.951 --> 26:04.737
Come on.
You got it.

26:04.780 --> 26:06.739
Josh, you got him?

26:06.782 --> 26:09.132
<i>♪ </i>

26:09.176 --> 26:10.830
Yeah, we're good.

26:10.873 --> 26:13.702
- Okay, you're up, Eve.
- Okay.

26:13.746 --> 26:15.878
- Okay, you got it.
Just one at a time.

26:15.922 --> 26:17.880
- Looking good.
- Easy.

26:17.924 --> 26:22.624
<i>♪ </i>

26:22.668 --> 26:26.019
- Just a few more rungs.
You got it, Eve.

26:26.062 --> 26:27.673
- Come on, Mom.
You can do this.

26:27.716 --> 26:30.110
Take my hand when you're here.
Take my hand.

26:30.153 --> 26:31.633
- Whoa!
- Whoa, Eve!

26:31.677 --> 26:32.808
Hold on!

26:32.852 --> 26:34.070
- Mom, grab my hand.
- Hold on!

26:34.114 --> 26:35.245
Reach out, okay?

26:35.289 --> 26:37.596
Mom, reach out
and grab my hand.

26:37.639 --> 26:38.945
- Mom!
- No!

26:38.988 --> 26:42.426
- Mom!
- Eve, hang on!

26:42.470 --> 26:45.168
- Mom, I got you.
I got you.

26:45.212 --> 26:48.955
Come on, come on.

26:48.998 --> 26:52.915
<i>♪ </i>

26:52.959 --> 26:53.960
You okay?

26:54.003 --> 26:55.048
Yeah, you okay?

26:55.091 --> 26:57.964
Yeah.

26:58.007 --> 26:59.705
What are we gonna do now?

26:59.748 --> 27:01.794
- You guys are gonna have
to move on without us.

27:01.837 --> 27:04.144
We're gonna make our way up
the mountain the long the way.

27:04.187 --> 27:06.146
I'll see you up there.

27:06.189 --> 27:10.933
<i>♪ </i>

27:10.977 --> 27:12.500
[police siren wailing]

27:12.543 --> 27:14.633
<i>- This is </i>
the Seattle Police Department.

27:14.676 --> 27:17.636
<i>You must evacuate </i>
the area now.

27:17.679 --> 27:18.985
- We gotta move
all these people down

27:19.028 --> 27:21.074
away from the bridge.

27:21.117 --> 27:25.992
[police siren wailing]

27:26.035 --> 27:28.255
<i>Evacuate the area.</i>

27:28.298 --> 27:31.127
You're all I have now, Lilly.

27:31.171 --> 27:33.608
Let's keep it moving.

27:33.652 --> 27:38.395
- You need to go.
Take the map to Isiah.

27:38.439 --> 27:44.271
[police siren wailing]

27:44.314 --> 27:48.536
- Ella, you saw something,
didn't you?

27:48.579 --> 27:50.973
My dad has the same look
when it happens to him.

27:51.017 --> 27:52.758
What did you see?

27:52.801 --> 27:55.021
- There's someone down there,
someone I was close to.

27:55.064 --> 27:56.718
She's in trouble.

27:56.762 --> 27:57.937
Okay.

27:57.980 --> 28:00.417
<i>Evacuate the area now.</i>

28:00.461 --> 28:02.202
<i>This is the </i>
Seattle Police Department.

28:02.245 --> 28:04.900
- Dad.
- Iz.

28:04.944 --> 28:07.033
Dad, it's getting worse.

28:07.076 --> 28:08.687
Hey, hang in there.

28:08.730 --> 28:10.123
- Gavin.
- Okay?

28:10.166 --> 28:12.734
- The area's been evacuated.
People should be safe.

28:12.778 --> 28:14.736
- When is this thing
gonna open?

28:14.780 --> 28:16.738
Oh, no.

28:16.782 --> 28:18.000
Sophia, what's wrong?

28:18.044 --> 28:19.741
- The seismic readings
in the area

28:19.785 --> 28:21.134
they're going down.

28:21.177 --> 28:22.570
- You're saying it's
not gonna happen?

28:22.613 --> 28:24.746
- I don't know.
- Damn it, Sophia.

28:24.790 --> 28:26.792
Do you realize what I put
on the line for this?

28:26.835 --> 28:28.707
Okay, this has gone far enough.
I'm shutting it down.

28:28.750 --> 28:31.187
- Wait, maybe it's gonna
open somewhere else.

28:31.231 --> 28:33.059
Let me see the map.

28:33.102 --> 28:34.887
<i>♪ </i>

28:34.930 --> 28:37.019
The map, it's fading.

28:37.063 --> 28:40.240
<i>♪ </i>

28:40.283 --> 28:42.677
How the hell did that happen?

28:42.721 --> 28:45.114
- I don't know.
- I think I do.

28:45.158 --> 28:46.463
Aldridge told me to get

28:46.507 --> 28:47.856
to the light
and bring the map to you.

28:47.900 --> 28:50.903
But I think this means
I may not make it.

28:50.946 --> 28:53.470
<i>♪ </i>

28:57.300 --> 28:58.606
I was right.

28:58.649 --> 28:59.781
The seismic activity
isn't going away.

28:59.825 --> 29:01.217
It's just shifting.

29:01.261 --> 29:03.045
There's a campground
12 miles east of here.

29:03.089 --> 29:05.047
Look at the readings.
They're getting stronger.

29:05.091 --> 29:07.136
- Okay, so we need to get
to that campground.

29:07.180 --> 29:11.010
<i>♪ </i>

29:11.053 --> 29:12.533
Let's go.

29:12.576 --> 29:17.407
<i>♪ </i>

29:17.451 --> 29:19.018
Sorry, I'm slowing us down.

29:19.061 --> 29:21.977
You're doing great, Josh.

29:22.021 --> 29:23.805
Look.

29:23.849 --> 29:27.461
This looks like the way out.

29:27.504 --> 29:34.642
<i>♪ </i>

29:35.861 --> 29:39.255
- We made it.
- Yeah, we have to hurry.

29:39.299 --> 29:41.692
Come on, come on.

29:41.736 --> 29:45.827
<i>♪ </i>

29:45.871 --> 29:47.611
- Please leave
your belongings--

29:47.655 --> 29:48.656
- Back to your vehicle
please, sir.

29:48.699 --> 29:50.179
- And head back
to your cars now.

29:50.223 --> 29:52.747
<i>♪ </i>

29:52.791 --> 29:54.183
- That sinkhole could open
at any moment.

29:54.227 --> 29:57.404
We gotta find it.
Iz, stay here.

29:57.447 --> 30:00.363
No, Dad, I can do it.

30:00.407 --> 30:02.713
Let me come with you.

30:02.757 --> 30:05.194
Okay, let's go.

30:05.238 --> 30:10.721
<i>♪ </i>

30:10.765 --> 30:12.245
- What are the readings
saying now?

30:12.288 --> 30:13.637
It's getting stronger.

30:13.681 --> 30:16.510
[distant rumbling]

30:16.553 --> 30:20.601
- Do you hear that?
- It came from over there.

30:20.644 --> 30:27.782
<i>♪ </i>

30:35.659 --> 30:37.792
This is it?

30:37.836 --> 30:41.013
<i>♪ </i>

30:41.056 --> 30:44.755
- Dad, I don't think you're
gonna get a plane down there.

30:44.799 --> 30:46.409
What are we gonna do?

30:46.453 --> 30:50.631
<i>♪ </i>

30:50.674 --> 30:54.853
- You need to stop, Lucas.
- No, no, we're almost there.

30:54.896 --> 30:58.291
- Please.
- Okay, okay, okay.

31:04.123 --> 31:06.081
Hey.

31:08.388 --> 31:10.869
I'm not gonna
let you die on me.

31:10.912 --> 31:13.784
It's not up to you.

31:13.828 --> 31:16.004
I need you
to promise me something.

31:16.048 --> 31:18.702
No, we're not doing this.

31:18.746 --> 31:21.357
Listen to me.

31:23.751 --> 31:28.538
Don't go back to your old life.
Make something of yourself.

31:28.582 --> 31:31.541
- Mom.
- Promise me.

31:31.585 --> 31:34.153
<i>[soft music]</i>

31:34.196 --> 31:37.634
- Okay, okay, okay.
Okay, I promise.

31:37.678 --> 31:40.420
I promise, okay?

31:40.463 --> 31:42.726
I promise.

31:42.770 --> 31:45.599
<i>♪ </i>

31:45.642 --> 31:48.471
I love you, Lucas.

31:48.515 --> 31:55.478
<i>♪ </i>

31:55.522 --> 31:58.307
- Mom?
Hey.

31:58.351 --> 32:02.311
Mom, Mom?

32:02.355 --> 32:05.880
Hey, no, no, no.

32:05.924 --> 32:08.361
No, no, no.

32:08.404 --> 32:12.147
No, no, no.

32:12.191 --> 32:16.586
Sam, Sam!

32:16.630 --> 32:18.458
Anybody, help!

32:18.501 --> 32:20.982
Help!

32:21.026 --> 32:23.854
<i>♪ </i>

32:23.898 --> 32:28.337
Come on, come on, come on,
come on.

32:28.381 --> 32:32.298
Get up, get up.

32:32.341 --> 32:34.735
Get up!

32:34.778 --> 32:39.566
<i>♪ </i>

32:39.609 --> 32:44.745
[sobbing]

32:44.788 --> 32:51.795
<i>♪ </i>

32:51.839 --> 32:53.928
- We're almost there.
Come on.

32:53.972 --> 32:57.279
- Keep going.
- [grunts]

32:57.323 --> 32:58.672
Josh, hey.

32:58.715 --> 33:02.502
<i>[tense music]</i>

33:02.545 --> 33:05.331
Iz.

33:05.374 --> 33:08.073
Just breathe.

33:08.116 --> 33:13.034
- Hey, hey, hey.
- Mom, go, go without me.

33:13.078 --> 33:16.429
You need to get him
through the light.

33:16.472 --> 33:19.649
- Okay.
- Go.

33:19.693 --> 33:21.651
I'm coming right back, okay?

33:21.695 --> 33:24.611
I know.

33:24.654 --> 33:26.569
You ready?

33:26.613 --> 33:28.528
<i>♪ </i>

33:28.571 --> 33:31.661
It's okay, Josh.

33:31.705 --> 33:35.665
You're gonna be all right.

33:35.709 --> 33:37.145
So are you.

33:37.189 --> 33:39.495
Come on, come on.

33:39.539 --> 33:46.459
<i>♪ </i>

33:53.205 --> 33:56.338
- Mom!
- No, Silas, let him go!

33:56.382 --> 33:58.340
Eve!

33:58.384 --> 33:59.559
Grandpa, no!

33:59.602 --> 34:01.039
No!

34:04.825 --> 34:07.654
- Grandpa!
Josh is gonna die.

34:07.697 --> 34:10.004
- I can't let you do this.
- Grandpa, please.

34:10.048 --> 34:11.962
Stop!

34:12.006 --> 34:13.486
[grunts]

34:13.529 --> 34:17.707
<i>[tense music]</i>

34:17.751 --> 34:19.274
- I'm taking Isiah
to the light.

34:19.318 --> 34:20.710
Don't try and stop me.

34:20.754 --> 34:24.018
- You take him up there,
the moment you go,

34:24.062 --> 34:25.889
I'll kill your son.

34:25.933 --> 34:31.417
<i>♪ </i>

34:31.460 --> 34:35.029
Give Isiah to me now.

34:35.073 --> 34:39.294
It's over, Silas.

34:39.338 --> 34:42.254
- You don't know
what you're doing.

34:42.297 --> 34:44.995
- I know I never
should have trusted you.

34:45.039 --> 34:48.216
- Mom, the light's
almost closed.

34:48.260 --> 34:52.177
- I've got him, Eve.
Go.

34:52.220 --> 34:54.875
<i>♪ </i>

34:54.918 --> 34:59.314
- I'm sorry, Grandpa.
I have to do this.

34:59.358 --> 35:01.577
I have to save Josh.

35:01.621 --> 35:04.580
<i>♪ </i>

35:04.624 --> 35:07.148
I love you.

35:07.192 --> 35:09.368
<i>♪ </i>

35:09.411 --> 35:11.370
Until we meet again, my boy.

35:11.413 --> 35:13.894
- Come on, come on.
Let's go.

35:13.937 --> 35:15.983
We gotta go.
We gotta go.

35:16.026 --> 35:22.946
<i>♪ </i>

35:33.043 --> 35:36.221
- You should go, too,
before it closes.

35:36.264 --> 35:38.484
<i>♪ </i>

35:38.527 --> 35:41.661
I'm not leaving.

35:41.704 --> 35:44.229
There's nothing for me in 1988.

35:44.272 --> 35:46.492
I go there, I still die.

35:46.535 --> 35:50.235
At least here,
I have a purpose,

35:50.278 --> 35:53.238
people I care about.

35:53.281 --> 35:56.241
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

35:56.284 --> 36:03.204
<i>♪ </i>

36:55.648 --> 36:58.607
Thank you.

36:58.651 --> 37:00.783
Goodbye, Eve.

37:00.827 --> 37:07.877
<i>♪ </i>

37:16.495 --> 37:19.672
Mom did it.

37:19.715 --> 37:22.109
How you feeling?

37:22.152 --> 37:25.068
- The pain is gone.
- Yeah?

37:25.112 --> 37:30.204
<i>♪ </i>

37:30.248 --> 37:32.293
So what now?

37:32.337 --> 37:34.426
- I've got a team coming
to secure the sinkhole.

37:34.469 --> 37:38.952
- Let's go.
- No, I'm not leaving.

37:38.995 --> 37:40.475
I can't let you do this.

37:40.519 --> 37:41.911
- It's not up to you.
- Gavin--

37:41.955 --> 37:43.870
- This is the last chance
I have to save my family.

37:43.913 --> 37:46.046
If you go, there's no way back.

37:46.089 --> 37:48.222
- I made it back once before.
I can do it again.

37:48.266 --> 37:50.006
- When you land,
you'll be in Seattle.

37:50.050 --> 37:52.357
That's 1,200 miles
from Los Angeles.

37:52.400 --> 37:53.619
How you gonna get there?

37:53.662 --> 37:56.535
- I don't know.
But I have to try.

37:56.578 --> 38:02.410
<i>♪ </i>

38:02.454 --> 38:06.675
Iz, I have to jump.

38:06.719 --> 38:08.329
I'm going, too.

38:08.373 --> 38:10.549
There's someone down there
I made a promise to.

38:10.592 --> 38:12.333
I have to go back for her.

38:12.377 --> 38:15.293
- Dad, I'm coming with you.
- No, Iz, Iz, you can't.

38:15.336 --> 38:18.513
We either go together,
or I'll jump right after you.

38:18.557 --> 38:20.515
Your choice.

38:20.559 --> 38:25.390
<i>♪ </i>

38:25.433 --> 38:28.697
Okay.

38:28.741 --> 38:31.047
Let's go together.

38:31.091 --> 38:32.397
Okay.

38:32.440 --> 38:37.315
<i>♪ </i>

38:37.358 --> 38:41.623
Thank you for everything.

38:41.667 --> 38:43.669
Good luck.

38:43.712 --> 38:50.806
<i>♪ </i>

39:03.341 --> 39:06.518
Josh!

39:06.561 --> 39:09.608
Are you all right?
You okay?

39:09.651 --> 39:11.261
- I'm good.
- Yeah?

39:11.305 --> 39:13.133
<i>♪ </i>

39:13.176 --> 39:15.701
- It's over.
You did it, Mom.

39:15.744 --> 39:18.312
No, no, we did it.

39:18.356 --> 39:21.402
You saved my life back there.
You're amazing.

39:21.446 --> 39:25.058
- What took you so long
to figure that out?

39:25.101 --> 39:30.237
- I guess I haven't always
seen things so clearly.

39:30.280 --> 39:31.804
And after what happened
with Izzy,

39:31.847 --> 39:33.458
I think I just--I thought

39:33.501 --> 39:35.547
I had to do everything
I could to protect you.

39:35.590 --> 39:39.464
And you didn't need that.

39:39.507 --> 39:43.555
- Eve, Josh!
- You guys okay?

39:43.598 --> 39:44.860
- Yeah, we're good.
We're good.

39:44.904 --> 39:46.732
- Isiah made it
through the light.

39:46.775 --> 39:47.863
Thank God.

39:47.907 --> 39:50.953
<i>♪ </i>

39:50.997 --> 39:52.868
- Appreciate you not
dying on me.

39:52.912 --> 39:58.178
<i>♪ </i>

39:58.221 --> 40:02.008
- Lilly, what are
you doing here?

40:02.051 --> 40:04.053
- Where's Isiah?
- He's gone, honey.

40:04.097 --> 40:05.925
No, no, he can't be.

40:05.968 --> 40:07.927
I have to give this
back to him.

40:07.970 --> 40:10.408
Lilly, Lilly.

40:10.451 --> 40:12.627
Hold on.

40:12.671 --> 40:14.803
Lilly!

40:14.847 --> 40:16.239
We've been walking all day.

40:16.283 --> 40:20.026
Where the hell
are you taking me?

40:20.069 --> 40:22.245
We're here, Scott.

40:22.289 --> 40:26.380
<i>♪ </i>

40:26.424 --> 40:29.339
Whoa.

40:29.383 --> 40:32.299
That's impossible.

40:32.342 --> 40:35.911
Someone built that here.

40:35.955 --> 40:41.482
Yes, I did.

40:41.526 --> 40:43.919
There's more you need to see.

40:43.963 --> 40:49.447
<i>♪ </i>

40:49.490 --> 40:51.013
Isiah!

40:51.057 --> 40:54.582
<i>[tense music]</i>

40:54.626 --> 40:56.802
He's not here anymore.

40:56.845 --> 41:02.721
<i>♪ </i>

41:02.764 --> 41:04.287
Now I'll never get home.

41:04.331 --> 41:06.986
<i>♪ </i>

41:07.029 --> 41:08.814
Hey, come on.

41:08.857 --> 41:11.294
We should go back
to the clearing.

41:11.338 --> 41:17.562
<i>♪ </i>

41:17.605 --> 41:19.433
What is that?

41:19.477 --> 41:22.436
<i>♪ </i>

41:22.480 --> 41:23.524
Josh?

41:23.568 --> 41:26.745
Riley!

41:26.788 --> 41:28.747
Riley.

41:28.790 --> 41:30.662
<i>♪ </i>

41:30.705 --> 41:32.838
- Where the hell
did they go?

41:32.881 --> 41:34.753
<i>♪ </i>

41:34.796 --> 41:36.711
Oh, my God.

41:36.755 --> 41:39.235
<i>♪ </i>

41:42.543 --> 41:45.459
<i>[soft music]</i>

41:45.503 --> 41:52.466
<i>♪ </i>

42:08.961 --> 42:11.964
Did we make it?

42:12.007 --> 42:14.009
[mammoth trumpets]

42:14.053 --> 42:17.012
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

42:17.056 --> 42:24.193
<i>♪ </i>

42:29.503 --> 42:33.028
[mammoth trumpets]

42:33.072 --> 42:38.556
<i>♪ </i>

42:38.599 --> 42:40.645
I think we made it.

42:40.688 --> 42:45.867
<i>♪ </i>

42:45.911 --> 42:47.826
Let's go find Mom and Josh.

42:47.869 --> 42:55.007
<i>♪ </i>

42:59.054 --> 43:02.014
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

43:02.057 --> 43:09.195
<i>♪ </i>
